    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_45f41381-9028-4dd5-a2b5-c22e25ca94cf",
      "del:text": "Hi , did everyone turn the last <CARD> cards ?",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_1"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_45f41381-9028-4dd5-a2b5-c22e25ca94cf"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_4e8d2980-250d-4551-886e-1a9efe88c6d2",
      "del:text": "The rule is : all cards with vowels on one side have an even number on the other , so the only card that needs to be checked is the one vowel card .",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_2"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_4e8d2980-250d-4551-886e-1a9efe88c6d2"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_fadee20f-55b2-43f9-b3a9-906bfcc36fd9",
      "del:text": "I think that only the cards with the <CARD> and the <CARD> are relevant to test the rule .",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_3"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_fadee20f-55b2-43f9-b3a9-906bfcc36fd9"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_7192a953-e2c7-4ed9-81d2-13b99d20c491",
      "del:text": "Right , the first <CARD> cards are applicable",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_1"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_7192a953-e2c7-4ed9-81d2-13b99d20c491"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_2d7ff88c-93bb-4a17-bbf3-dbda647b4644",
      "del:text": "'The <CARD> does not need to be turned . The rule doesn''t say that even numbers have a vowel on the other side .'",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_2"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_2d7ff88c-93bb-4a17-bbf3-dbda647b4644"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_4b1a6951-92a7-4898-a919-efbfe34476bf",
      "del:text": "If we turn the <CARD> , we can see if it has a vowel , which would further test the rule",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_3"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_4b1a6951-92a7-4898-a919-efbfe34476bf"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_1d1cdd12-5302-43ea-9117-de1eec9987ce",
      "del:text": "It only says vowels have even numbers . Even numbers could possibly have consonants on the other side .",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_2"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_1d1cdd12-5302-43ea-9117-de1eec9987ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_fed4f3c7-921a-4e74-9d41-4a160b716337",
      "del:text": "This is true , if you want to test the actual rule , you have to flip the first two",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_4"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_fed4f3c7-921a-4e74-9d41-4a160b716337"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_94f336d9-97c6-4b14-902d-7dbd1d41eef0",
      "del:text": "'No it wouldn''t . It doesn''t say , even numbers only have vowels , it says vowels have even numbers .'",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_2"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_94f336d9-97c6-4b14-902d-7dbd1d41eef0"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_4ee301b9-2ebb-4146-bb21-8fd61faa36e5",
      "del:text": "And vice versa . Both apply to the rule .",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_3"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_4ee301b9-2ebb-4146-bb21-8fd61faa36e5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_4e02ed02-f4b9-4aba-befe-69b37935995e",
      "del:text": "'That''s why I flipped the last <CARD> cards , for the first <CARD> cards to follow the rule'",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_1"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_4e02ed02-f4b9-4aba-befe-69b37935995e"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_31bf8eb7-ea08-442f-a9fe-d7608dea6ee2",
      "del:text": "If we needed to turn over the <CARD> , it would say even nyumbers only have vowels .",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_2"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_31bf8eb7-ea08-442f-a9fe-d7608dea6ee2"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_2d62c268-11a0-4fdb-8141-7afee4f52b6e",
      "del:text": "It does say vowels have an even number . That would also mean even numbers would have vowels .",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_3"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
        "@id": "delidata_argument_2d62c268-11a0-4fdb-8141-7afee4f52b6e"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Contribution",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_message_950033be-e98f-4517-8d7d-17af6a691815",
      "del:text": "The problem is that it could",
      "del:madeBy": {
        "@id": "participant_4"
      },
      "del:hasTopic": {
        "@id": "delidata_topic_cc4fa8e4-2d8b-44d2-b3a5-fe569a488397"
      },
      "del:hasArgument": {
